  "sections": {
    "Description": "Crabs fire aScarab-like artillery attack that reaches up to five tiles in range. The projectile damages both the tile it lands on and one tile in front of it. Despite being named after an aquatic animal, it is capable of drowning.\nCrabs cannot appear on the first island and are limited to two spawns, includingits alpha, per mission. Crabs also cannot appear with Scarabs orMoths.",
    "Strategy": "Crabs are slightly more durable than the Scarab but the strategy remains the same; if you cannot kill it you push it away. The extra area from the projectile means pushing it away from the target is unsafe, but pushing it towards or to the side will usually be fine.\nThough it is not shown in game, keep in mind that Crabs have a maximum 5-tile range. If possible to do so safely, pushing them towards the edges is encouraged, as it will force them to move forwards to target buildings at the other end of the map. The player can use this knowledge to their advantage by walling them out and limiting the possible targets that Crabs can hit, making their movements more predictable."
  },
  "full_text": "Crab\nDetails\nHealth\n3\nMove\n3\nSystems\nExplosive Expulsions\n(\nEnemy\n)\nEffect\nLaunch artillery attack on 2 tiles for 1 damage (5 tile range).\nThe\nCrab\nis a rare\nVek\nfrom\nInto The Breach\n.\nDescription\n[\n]\nCrabs fire a\nScarab\n-like artillery attack that reaches up to five tiles in range. The projectile damages both the tile it lands on and one tile in front of it. Despite being named after an aquatic animal, it is capable of drowning.\nCrabs cannot appear on the first island and are limited to two spawns, including\nits alpha\n, per mission. Crabs also cannot appear with Scarabs or\nMoths\n.\nStrategy\n[\n]\nCrabs are slightly more durable than the Scarab but the strategy remains the same; if you cannot kill it you push it away. The extra area from the projectile means pushing it away from the target is unsafe, but pushing it towards or to the side will usually be fine.\nThough it is not shown in game, keep in mind that Crabs have a maximum 5-tile range. If possible to do so safely, pushing them towards the edges is encouraged, as it will force them to move forwards to target buildings at the other end of the map. The player can use this knowledge to their advantage by walling them out and limiting the possible targets that Crabs can hit, making their movements more predictable.\nv\n\u00b7\nd\n\u00b7\ne\nVek\nVek\nBeetle\n\u2022\nBlobber\n\u2022\nBurrower\n\u2022\nCentipede\n\u2022\nCrab\n\u2022\nDigger\n\u2022\nFirefly\n\u2022\nHornet\n\u2022\nLeaper\n\u2022\nScarab\n\u2022\nScorpion\n\u2022\nSpider\n\u2022\nVolatile Vek\nVek (Advanced Edition)\nBouncer\n\u2022\nGastropod\n\u2022\nMosquito\n\u2022\nMoth\n\u2022\nPlasmodia\n\u2022\nStarfish\n\u2022\nTumblebug\nAlpha Vek\nAlpha Beetle\n\u2022\nAlpha Blobber\n\u2022\nAlpha Burrower\n\u2022\nAlpha Centipede\n\u2022\nAlpha Crab\n\u2022\nAlpha Digger\n\u2022\nAlpha Firefly\n\u2022\nAlpha Hornet\n\u2022\nAlpha Leaper\n\u2022\nAlpha Scarab\n\u2022\nAlpha Scorpion\n\u2022\nAlpha Spider\nAlpha Vek (Advanced Edition)\nAlpha Bouncer\n\u2022\nAlpha Gastropod\n\u2022\nAlpha Mosquito\n\u2022\nAlpha Moth\n\u2022\nAlpha Plasmodia\n\u2022\nAlpha Starfish\n\u2022\nAlpha Tumblebug\nVek Psions\nBlast Psion\n\u2022\nBlood Psion\n\u2022\nShell Psion\n\u2022\nSoldier Psion\nVek Psions (Advanced Edition)\nArachnid Psion\n\u2022\nRaging Psion\n\u2022\nSmoldering Psion\nVek Minions\nBlob\n\u2022\nAlpha Blob\n\u2022\nSpiderling Egg\n\u2022\nSpiderling\n\u2022\nAlpha Spiderling\nVek Minions (Advanced Edition)\nSpore\n\u2022\nAlpha Spore\n\u2022\nVicious Spore\n\u2022\nBlob Leader\nVek Leaders\nBeetle Leader\n\u2022\nFirefly Leader\n\u2022\nHornet Leader\n\u2022\nLarge Goo\n(\nMedium Goo\n) (\nSmall Goo\n) \u2022\nPsion Abomination\n\u2022\nScorpion Leader\n\u2022\nSpider Leader\nVek Leaders (Advanced Edition)\nBlobber Leader\n\u2022\nBouncer Leader\n\u2022\nCentipede Leader\n\u2022\nCrab Leader\n\u2022\nGastropod Leader\n\u2022\nMosquito Leader\n\u2022\nPlasmodia Leader\n\u2022\nScarab Leader\n\u2022\nStarfish Leader\n\u2022\nTumblebug Leader",
